Aim  
To design and implement a Digital Clock and Timer Application using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript that displays the real-time clock and allows users to start, stop, and reset a timer.  
  
Procedure  
1.	Identify the requirement to create a Digital Clock and Timer application.   
  
2.	Create three files for the project:   
•	digital-clock.html   
•	style.css   
•	script.js   
  
3.	In the HTML file, create the basic structure using:   
  
•	<!DOCTYPE html>   
•	<html>   
•	<head>   
•	<body>   
  
4.	Set the title as Digital Clock / Timer.   
  
5.	Add a <div> element with id "clock" to display the real-time clock.   
  
6.	Add another <div> with id "timer" to display the timer.   
  
7.	Add three buttons:   
•	Start   
•	Stop   
•	Reset   
  
8.	Link the CSS file using <link> tag.   
9.	Link the JavaScript file using <script> tag with defer.   
  
10.	In CSS file:   
•	Style the body with dark background   
•	Center the content   
•	Style clock and timer boxes   
•	Style buttons   
  	  
11.	In JavaScript file:   
•	Use setInterval() to update the clock every second   
•	Create a timer using a seconds counter   
•	Implement Start, Stop, Reset functions   
•	Update the DOM dynamically   
  
12.	Save all files and open the HTML file in a browser.   
  
13.	Test the application by clicking Start, Stop, and Reset buttons.   
  
